An Act relating to the Statewide Recovery Fund;
making transfers from funds appropriated to the
Department of Human Services to the Statewide
Recovery Fund; making a transfer from funds
appropriated to the Health Care Workforce Development
Revolving Fund to the Statewide Recovery Fund; making
a transfer from funds appropriated to the Oklahoma
State University Medical Authority to the Statewide
Recovery Fund; making a transfer from funds
appropriated to the State Department of Health to the
Statewide Recovery Fund; making a transfer of funds
appropriated to the Department of Mental Health and
Substance Abuse Services to the Statewide Recovery
Fund; making a transfer of funds appropriated to the
Oklahoma Water Resources Board to the Statewide
Recovery Fund; determining all transfers are
consistent with specific joint committee actions;
providing for noncodification; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: Statewide Recovery Fund
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Two Million Eight Hundred Thousand Dollars
($2,800,000.00) appropriated from the Statewide Recovery Fund
created in Section 255 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to the

Department of Human Services by Section 2 of Enrolled House Bill No.
2884 of the 1st Regular Session of the 59th Oklahoma Legislature, to
provide semi-independent housing, food security, and transitional
tools to victims of domestic violence, the sum of One Million Five
Hundred Sixty Thousand Eight Hundred Seventy-five Dollars
($1,560,875.00) shall be transferred to the Statewide Recovery Fund
for reappropriation. Such transfer shall be consistent with the
recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief
Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Twelve Million Eight Hundred Two Thousand Nine Hundred
Ninety-three Dollars ($12,802,993.00) appropriated from the
Statewide Recovery Fund created in Section 255 of Title 62 of the
Oklahoma Statutes, to the Department of Human Services by Section 1
of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1186 of the 1st Regular Session of the
59th Oklahoma Legislature to establish a grant program that provides
assistance to food programs which support the availability of and
access to affordable and nutritious foods, the sum of One Hundred
Sixty-two Thousand Six Hundred Sixty-eight Dollars and eighty-five
cents ($162,668.85) shall be transferred to the Statewide Recovery
Fund for reappropriation. Such transfer shall be consistent with
the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic
Relief Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Four Million Five Hundred Thirty-seven Thousand Five
Hundred Dollars ($4,537,500.00) appropriated from the Statewide
Recovery Fund created in Section 255 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma
Statutes, to the Health Care Workforce Development Revolving Fund by
Section 7 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1458 of the 2nd Regular
Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature to establish a grant
program with Care Providers Oklahoma for the purpose of recruiting,
educating, and stabilizing Oklahoma's health care workforce, the sum
of One Million Four Hundred Ninety Thousand Six Hundred Seventy-five
Dollars and eight cents ($1,490,675.08) shall be transferred to the
Statewide Recovery Fund for reappropriation. Such transfer shall be
consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee
on Pandemic Relief Funding on May 12, 2025.
