SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Ten Million Dollars ($10,000,000.00) appropriated from
the Statewide Recovery Fund created in Section 255 of Title 62 of
the Oklahoma Statutes, to the Oklahoma State University Medical
Authority by Section 3 of Enrolled House Bill No. 1012 of the 2nd
Extraordinary Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature to fund
outreach, training, and other allowable expenses associated with the
implementation of a rural advanced care pilot program, the sum of
Two Million One Hundred Sixty-four Thousand Thirty-nine Dollars
($2,164,039.00) shall be transferred to the Statewide Recovery Fund
for reappropriation. Such transfer shall be consistent with the
recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief
Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Twenty-five Million Dollars ($25,000,000.00) appropriated
from the Statewide Recovery Fund created in Section 255 of Title 62
of the Oklahoma Statutes, to the State Department of Health by
Section 3 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 20 of the 2nd Extraordinary
Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature for a program providing
medical facilities for disproportionately impacted populations, the
sum of Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000.00) shall be transferred to
the Statewide Recovery Fund for reappropriation. Such transfer
shall be consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint
Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Eighty-seven Million Dollars ($87,000,000.00)
appropriated from the Statewide Recovery Fund created in Section 255
of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to the Department of Mental
Health and Substance Abuse Services by Section 1 of Enrolled House
Bill No. 1013 of the 2nd Extraordinary Session of the 58th Oklahoma
Legislature for addressing the ongoing increased demand for mental
health services by constructing a replacement facility for Griffin
Memorial Hospital; provided, that such construction be confined
within a thirty-mile radius of the State Capitol Building, the sum
of Twenty Million Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($20,500,000.00)
shall be transferred to the Statewide Recovery Fund for
reappropriation. Such transfer shall be consistent with the
