recommendations adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief
Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Eight Million Dollars ($8,000,000.00) appropriated from
the Statewide Recovery Fund created in Section 255 of Title 62 of
the Oklahoma Statutes, to the Oklahoma Water Resources Board by
Section 9 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 13 of the 2nd Extraordinary
Session of the 58th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Three Million
Three Hundred Thousand Dollars ($3,300,000.00) shall be transferred
to the Statewide Recovery Fund for reappropriation. Such transfer
shall be consistent with the recommendations adopted by the Joint
Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on May 12, 2025.
SECTION 8. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
SECTION 9. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
